%% KubeRay Operator - Data Flow Diagram
%% Generated by: Claude Opus 4.6
%% Source: architecture/rhoai-2.6/kuberay.md

sequenceDiagram
    participant User as User / Data Scientist
    participant K8sAPI as Kubernetes API<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+
    participant Operator as kuberay-operator<br/>ServiceAccount Token
    participant HeadPod as Ray Head Pod<br/>Dashboard: 8265/TCP
    participant Workers as Ray Worker Pods
    participant BatchJob as K8s Batch Job Pod
    participant ServeSvc as Serve Service<br/>8000/TCP
    participant Client as External Client

    Note over User,Client: Flow 1: RayCluster Provisioning
    User->>K8sAPI: kubectl apply RayCluster CR<br/>HTTPS/443, Bearer Token
    K8sAPI-->>Operator: Watch event (RayCluster created)
    Operator->>K8sAPI: Create Head Pod<br/>HTTPS/443, SA Token
    Operator->>K8sAPI: Create Head Service<br/>(6379, 8265, 8000, 8080, 10001)
    Operator->>K8sAPI: Create Worker Pods<br/>HTTPS/443, SA Token
    Operator->>K8sAPI: Create Route/Ingress<br/>(if enableIngress: true)

    Note over User,Client: Flow 2: RayJob Submission
    User->>K8sAPI: kubectl apply RayJob CR<br/>HTTPS/443, Bearer Token
    K8sAPI-->>Operator: Watch event (RayJob created)
    Operator->>K8sAPI: Create/Get RayCluster<br/>HTTPS/443, SA Token
    Operator->>HeadPod: GET /api/jobs/ (check readiness)<br/>HTTP/8265, plaintext, No Auth
    Operator->>K8sAPI: Create K8s Batch Job<br/>HTTPS/443, SA Token
    BatchJob->>HeadPod: Submit job via ray CLI<br/>HTTP/8265, plaintext, No Auth
    HeadPod->>Workers: Distribute tasks
    loop Poll until complete
        Operator->>HeadPod: GET /api/jobs/ (poll status)<br/>HTTP/8265, plaintext, No Auth
    end
    HeadPod-->>Operator: Job status (SUCCEEDED/FAILED)
    Operator->>K8sAPI: Update RayJob status

    Note over User,Client: Flow 3: RayService Serve Deployment
    User->>K8sAPI: kubectl apply RayService CR<br/>HTTPS/443, Bearer Token
    K8sAPI-->>Operator: Watch event (RayService created)
    Operator->>K8sAPI: Create active RayCluster<br/>HTTPS/443, SA Token
    Operator->>HeadPod: PUT /api/serve/applications/<br/>HTTP/8265, plaintext, No Auth
    HeadPod-->>Operator: Deployment status
    loop Health check
        Operator->>HeadPod: GET /api/serve/applications/<br/>HTTP/8265, plaintext, No Auth
        HeadPod-->>Operator: Serve health status
    end
    Operator->>K8sAPI: Create serve-svc Service<br/>HTTPS/443, SA Token
    Client->>ServeSvc: Inference request<br/>HTTP/8000, plaintext, No Auth
    ServeSvc-->>Client: Inference response
